Package org.jsweet.transpiler

Interface JSweetOptions

All Known Implementing Classes:
JSweetTranspiler
public interface JSweetOptions
This interface holds all the JSweet transpiler configuration and options.
Author:
Renaud Pawlak

  • Method Details

    • getConfiguration

      Map<String,​Object> getConfiguration()
      Returns the configuration from the configuration file.

    • isPreserveSourceLineNumbers

      @Deprecated boolean isPreserveSourceLineNumbers()
      Deprecated.
      use isGenerateSourceMaps() instead
      Tells if the transpiler generates js.map files for Java debugging.

    • isGenerateSourceMaps

      boolean isGenerateSourceMaps()
      Tells if the transpiler generates js.map files for Java debugging.

    • getSourceRoot

      File getSourceRoot()
      Gets the source root for the source map files. Use this option if the Java source is located in a different place at runtime.

    • getTsOutputDir

      File getTsOutputDir()
      Gets the current TypeScript output directory.

    • getJsOutputDir

      File getJsOutputDir()
      Gets the current JavaScript output directory.

    • getDeclarationsOutputDir

      File getDeclarationsOutputDir()
      Gets the current .d.ts output directory (only if the declaration option is set).

      By default, declarations are placed in the JavaScript output directory.

    • getModuleKind

      ModuleKind getModuleKind()
      Gets the module kind when transpiling to code using JavaScript modules.

    • isBundle

      boolean isBundle()
      Tells if this transpiler generates JavaScript bundles for running in a Web browser.

    • getEncoding

      String getEncoding()
      Gets the expected Java source code encoding.

    • getOutEncoding

      String getOutEncoding()
      Gets the encoding of generated TypeScript files.

    • isNoRootDirectories

      boolean isNoRootDirectories()
      Tells if this transpiler skips the root directories (packages annotated with @jsweet.lang.Root) so that the generated file hierarchy starts at the root directories rather than including the entire directory structure.

    • isIgnoreAssertions

      boolean isIgnoreAssertions()
      Tells if the transpiler should ignore the 'assert' statements or generate appropriate code.

    • isIgnoreJavaFileNameError

      boolean isIgnoreJavaFileNameError()
      Generates output code even if the main class is not placed within a file of the same name.

    • isGenerateDeclarations

      boolean isGenerateDeclarations()
      Generates d.ts files along with the js files.

    • getExtractedCandyJavascriptDir

      File getExtractedCandyJavascriptDir()
      The directory where the transpiler should put the extracted JavaScript files from candies. Candies can bundle one or more JavaScript files that will be extracted to this directory.

    • isGenerateJsFiles

      boolean isGenerateJsFiles()
      If false, do not compile TypeScript output (let an external TypeScript compiler do so). Default is true.

    • isGenerateTsFiles

      boolean isGenerateTsFiles()
      If false, do not generate TypeScript output (just validate the Java source code and do not transpile anything). Default is true.

    • isGenerateDefinitions

      boolean isGenerateDefinitions()
      Generated definitions from def.* packages in d.ts files.

    • isIgnoreTypeScriptErrors

      boolean isIgnoreTypeScriptErrors()
      If true, JSweet will ignore any message reported by TypeScript (including error) and the compilation will be successful if no Java error is raised.

    • isIgnoreJavaErrors

      boolean isIgnoreJavaErrors()
      If true, JSweet will ignore any message reported by Java (including error). Do not use unless you know what you are doing.

    • getHeaderFile

      File getHeaderFile()
      Gets the file containing the header to be added to the generated files.
      Returns:
      the header file, null if undefined

    • isDebugMode

      boolean isDebugMode()
      If true, the transpiler generates code that can be debugged with JavaScript.

    • isVerbose

      boolean isVerbose()
      If true, JSweet has been launched in verbose mode.

    • isDisableSinglePrecisionFloats

      boolean isDisableSinglePrecisionFloats()
      By default, for a target version >=ES5, JSweet will force Java floats to be mapped to JavaScript numbers that will be constrained with the Math.fround function. If this option is true, then the calls to Math.fround are erased and the generated program will use the JavaScript default precision (double precision).

    • getEcmaTargetVersion

      EcmaScriptComplianceLevel getEcmaTargetVersion()
      The targeted ECMAScript version.

    • getAdapters

      List<String> getAdapters()
      A list of adapter class names (fully qualified) to be used to extend the transpiler behavior. As the name suggests, an adapter is an instance of PrinterAdapter that adapts the TypeScript default printer in order to tune the generated code. All the adapter classes must be accessible within the 'jsweet_extension' directory to be created at the root of the transpiled project. The adapter classes can be provided as Java class files (*.class) or Java source files (*.java). In the latter case, they will be on-the-fly compiled by JSweet.
      See Also:
      PrinterAdapter

    • getModuleResolution

      ModuleResolution getModuleResolution()
      Determines how modules get resolved. Either "Node" for Node.js/io.js style resolution, or "Classic". See Tsc's Module Resolution documentation for more details.
      Returns:
      the current module resolution strategy

    • getConfigurationFile

      File getConfigurationFile()
      The configuration file, which is by default the jsweetconfig.json file in the current project.

    • isUsingModules

      boolean isUsingModules()
      Returns:
      true if module is set to somethind else than ModuleKind.none

    • isSkipTypeScriptChecks

      boolean isSkipTypeScriptChecks()

    • isTscWatchMode

      boolean isTscWatchMode()
      Returns:
      true to enable tsc watch mode

    • isLazyInitializedStatics

      boolean isLazyInitializedStatics()
      True (default) if JSweet generates code that lazily initializes statics in order to avoid initialization precedence issues (emulates Java behavior).

    • isUseSingleQuotesForStringLiterals

      boolean isUseSingleQuotesForStringLiterals()
      Generates string literals with single quotes rather than double quotes.
      Returns:
      true if activated

    • isNonEnumerableTransients

      boolean isNonEnumerableTransients()
      If true, the transpiler generates Java transient fields as non-enumerable JavaScript properties.

    • getHangingTscTimeout

      int getHangingTscTimeout()
      The duration in seconds after which a transpilation of a TypeScript file to JavaScript is considered to be hanging. By default the compilation is aborted after 10 seconds.

    • isSortClassMembers

      boolean isSortClassMembers()
      If true, class members are sorted using PrinterAdapter.getClassMemberComparator().

    • isAutoPropagateAsyncAwaits

      boolean isAutoPropagateAsyncAwaits()
      If true, auto propagates async methods and await invocations.

    • getJavaCompilerExtraOptions

      String[] getJavaCompilerExtraOptions()
      Gets additional options passed to the Java Compiler.
